b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av154.htm)  [Next](av156.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 74. Charm to allay discord.\n\n1\\. May your bodies be united, may your mindg and your purposes (be united)!\nBrahmanaspati here has brought you together, Bhaga has brought you together.  \n2\\. Harmony of mind (I procure) for you, and also harmony of heart. Moreover\nwith the aid of Bhaga's exertions do I cause you to agree.  \n3\\. As the \xc3\x82dityas are united with the Vasus, as the fierce (Rudras), free\nfrom grudge, with the Maruts, thus, O three-named (Agni), without grudge, do\nthou render these people here of the same mind!\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VII, 52. Charm against strife and bloodshed](av156.htm)\n\n"